					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">jwdonal wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">are you saying that accesses to the BSP should not show up on the external PPU address bus?</div>
<br />I'm pretty sure that the PPU's internal CGRAM accesses during rendering do not show up on the PPU bus. Ordinarily, the PPU accesses external memory only on every other dot, and the rated memory access speed of (say) CHR RAM bears this out. But it accesses CGRAM on every dot. (BSP is <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_space_partitioning" class="postlink">something else entirely</a>.)</div>

