				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">During sprite fetch (x=256 to 319), A12 is low for 4 dots (while performing a dummy nametable fetch) and high for 4 dots (while fetching the pattern). It is believed that the MMC3 puts some sort of low-pass filter between A12 and the scanline counter to ignore rising edges that occur less than 8 dots or so after a falling edge.</div>

